 by ecotheology has already been realized. While making this powerful argument, Dalton and Simmons also provide an essential overview of key ecotheological thinkers and texts  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aEcotheology. 0aKnowledge, Sociology of. 4aEnvironmental Studies : Ecology. 4aEnvironmental Studies : Environmental Philosophy. 4aEnvironmental Studies : Environmental Studies. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Theology. 7aRELIGION / Christian Theology / General.2bisacsh1 aSimmons, Henry C., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781438432984?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438432984423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438432984/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles